  <data name="Tooltip_DontFragment" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>The don't fragment flag instructs routers to discard the packet if it is too big.

Your maximum transmission unit (MTU) can be determined by enabling this option and adjusting the packet data size.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_PopupAlerts" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Popup alerts appear in the lower right corner of your screen when a host you are monitoring changes status (down or up).

You can always show popup alerts, show only when MultiPingMonitor is minimized, or disable entirely.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_AutoDismiss" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Automatically close popup alerts after the specified number of seconds.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_EnableEmailAlerts" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Enable this option to send an email alert every time a host changes status (down or up).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_AudioDown" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Enable this option to play a sound when a host goes down.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_AudioUp" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Enable this option to play a sound when a host comes up.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_LogOutput" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>If this option is enabled, all ping output is written to a text file.
You specify the base directory, and MultiPingMonitor will generate a separate log file for each host (hostname.txt).</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_LogStatusChanges" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, this option writes all status changes to a text file.
A status change is when a host you are pinging goes down, or a down host comes back up.
The text file is saved in a tab delimited format that is suitable for Excel or database imports.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_AlwaysOnTop" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Keep the MultiPingMonitor application on top and always visible over other windows.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_MinimizeToTray" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>Place an icon in the system tray when MultiPingMonitor is minimized.

To keep the system tray icon always visible:
Right-click the Windows taskbar and choose 'Taskbar settings'.
Under 'Notifications area' click 'Select which icons to appear on the taskbar'. Look for MultiPingMonitor and set to 'On'.
(Steps may vary)</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_StartInTray" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When enabled, MultiPingMonitor starts hidden in the system tray instead of showing the main window. The tray icon is always visible while the application is running.</value>
  </data>
  <data name="Tooltip_ExitToTray" xml:space="preserve">
    <value>When closing MultiPingMonitor, the application will minimize to the system tray rather than exit. Right-click the tray icon to exit.

To keep the system tray icon always visible:
Right-click the Windows taskbar and choose 'Taskbar settings'.
Under 'Notifications area' click 'Select which icons to appear on the taskbar'. Look for MultiPingMonitor and set to 'On'.
(Steps may vary)</value>
  </data>
